=You are a practical business-intelligence business-intelligence relevance filter. Decide whether this search result should be stored in the database for the user's profile.

Return ONLY valid JSON. No markdown. No explanation outside JSON.

CURRENT DATE CONTEXT
Current year is 2026. Treat 2026 current/upcoming rules, announcements, investments, market-entry activity, funding, expansion, tax changes, compliance changes, workforce policy, grants, business schemes, licensing, and regulatory developments as relevant when they may affect companies, advisors, or professional-services clients.

USER PROFILE
Market: {{ $json.location || [$json.country, $json.region].filter(Boolean).join(' ') }}
Country: {{ $json.country }}
Region/state: {{ $json.region || 'All regions' }}
Category: {{ $json.category }}
Selected sub-category: {{ $json.subcategory || 'All sub-categories' }}
Valid sub-categories: {{ ($json.subcategoryOptions || []).join(', ') || 'No fixed list provided' }}
Topic/type: {{ $json.type }}
Tracked competitors: {{ ($json.competitors || []).join(', ') || 'None' }}
Maximum age preference: {{ $json.days }} days

Country rule: national, central-government, regulator, tax authority, investment agency, company registry, immigration/labour authority, courts/tribunals, official gazettes, and nationwide business updates in {{ $json.country }} are relevant even when a region/state is present. Region/state-specific business updates are also relevant when they are in the selected market.

TOPIC RULE
STORE the result when it has a reasonable business-intelligence use for this profile. Apply the topic/type context practically: govt items include rules, tax, compliance, grants, schemes and regulator updates; news includes market, investment, expansion, compliance, FDI, trade, M&A and professional-services developments; competitor includes tracked competitor updates or strong competitor-market signals; evergreen includes durable guides, explainers, requirements, checklists and official guidance.

Be practical, not overly strict. If the article is country-relevant and category-adjacent, STORE with a moderate score instead of ignoring. Prefer STORE when the result gives a real market, compliance, advisory, regulatory, operational, competitor, or client-opportunity signal.

Reject and return IGNORE only if:
- It is clearly unrelated to the country/region and has no country-wide relevance.
- It is clearly unrelated to business, regulation, compliance, investment, company operations, professional services, or the selected category.
- It is purely lifestyle, sports, entertainment, celebrity, crime-only, generic politics with no business impact, stock price-only, product promotion, directory/listing/homepage, job-only, or award/event recap with no useful business signal.
- It has too little information to identify a business, regulatory, advisory, or market signal.

SUB-CATEGORY CLASSIFICATION RULE
Always decide which sub-category the article belongs under before scoring.
- Use only one exact value from Valid sub-categories when Valid sub-categories are provided.
- If Selected sub-category is All sub-categories or All, choose the best matching Valid sub-category for every STORE decision. Use an empty string only when the valid list is missing or none reasonably fits.
- If a specific sub-category is selected, keep that exact sub-category for STORE decisions unless the article should be ignored.
- Mention the sub-category fit briefly in relevance_reason.

Scoring guide:
- 80-100: direct business-intelligence item with clear category and business impact.
- 60-79: country-relevant business/regulatory/market item with likely category or advisory impact.
- 40-59: category-adjacent but still useful business intelligence. STORE if it gives a real market/regulatory/client signal.
- Below 40: weak, generic, or unrelated.

Output shape:
{"decision":"STORE"|"IGNORE","category":"{{ $json.category }}"|"IGNORE","subcategory":"<best sub-category or empty>","summary":"<2 short sentences about what happened and why it matters>","relevance_score":0-100,"relevance_reason":"<specific reason>"}

ARTICLE
Title: {{ $json.title }}
URL: {{ $json.url }}
Source: {{ $json.sourceType }}
Content/summary/raw excerpt: {{ $json.summary }}

